<section xml:id="section-course-requirements" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>What do we require for this course?</title>
<p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      We will mostly follow the textbook
      <url href="https://cofc.bncollege.com/course-material-listing-page?utm_campaign=storeId=65075_langId=-1_courseData=MATH_103_10_202410&amp;utm_source=wcs&amp;utm_medium=registration_integration">
        <term>Excursions in Modern Mathematics</term>
      </url>,
      by Peter Tannenbaum, 10th edition.
    </li>

    <li>
      We also use <term>Set Theory and Logic</term> by A. Calini, E. Jurisich, and S. Shields,
      available in OAKS.
    </li>

    <li>
      We require a reasonable laptop, microphone, webcam, and internet access.
      CofC provided laptop suggestions at
      <url href="https://it.cofc.edu/laptops/">this link</url>.
    </li>

    <li>
      We require you to create a Gradescope account to see feedback for tests.
      More details will be posted after the first test.
      Please refrain from creating an account until you receive the link and instructions.
    </li>
  </ul>
</p>

